  "prompt": "What's the Chabad view on lesbians?",
  "response": "Chabad, as a movement within Orthodox Judaism, holds traditional beliefs regarding issues of sexuality and gender, including views on lesbianism. Orthodox Judaism considers same-sex relationships, including lesbian relationships, to be contrary to Halacha (Jewish law). \n\nThe perspective is grounded in interpretations of biblical texts, such as the prohibition against same-sex sexual activities found in Leviticus. However, it's important to note that Chabad, like many Orthodox Jewish communities, emphasizes compassion, respect, and the inherent dignity of every individual. \n\nWhile upholding traditional beliefs, many Chabad communities strive to approach sensitive issues with empathy and care, prioritizing a welcoming and respectful environment for all Jews to engage in Jewish life and community. The approach can vary within the movement, and individual leaders and communities may handle the topic with different nuances.",
